< text>
So delicious!! We got the Oxtail dinner (pic 1)and jerk chicken dinner (pic two without the drink) and it was amazing. The oxtail and chicken were so soft and came right off the bone . The flavors took us back to the Jamaican village we visited years ago. And the beef patties (not pictured) had the most delicious, flaky crust that melted in your mouth and tasted like the homemade patties we used to get. We did have to wait longer than their quotes average for the food, but it was worth every second.< /text>

< username>
Mary Born< /username>
<Date>1616196057926</Date><rating>5<//rating>< Review>
Hilltop Jamaican Market is a great Black-owned and operated family market and restaurant. I overheard the family talking about a new location coming to Los Angeles soon!

Come for the amazing smells of goat curry and fresh meat pies. Oder a soursop nectar, or smoothie, or a large banquet meal. They do catering too.

Stock up on fresh, frozen and pantry items, and Jamaican imports.

Scotch bonnets (habanero) jerk spices and rubs, fresh coconut, dried plantains, oatmeal porridge from trinidad.

I loved the Bob marley collage posters, the food I made with ingredients I bought here, and the social distancing guidelines. Chefs, Jamaican food lovers, check this place out.</Review>

< Rate>

<Review>JAMAICA üáØüá≤
Excerpt from Eat the World Los Angeles:
Hilltop's has had quite a makeover since the beginning and is now humming along in its 27th year of business. Beloved by its neighbors in Pomona, you might also find that your fellow customers have driven from parts of Los Angeles because they prefer the food here to those located nearer to their homes.

The menu is full of all the favorites, which can be purchased as meals that include Jamaican rice and peas, cabbage or spinach, festival and plantains. The "small" portion is probably already large enough for two people when it arrives, the large is more fit for a family. If this is not enough meat, they also sell 32 ounce "cups" of each.< /Review>< pics>

No greetings when my family and I walked in. It seemed as if we were interrupting their day. 1st time visiting and the offer to answer any of the questions we may have regarding the menu was not asked. I opted out on trying anything but a Turkey burger because I still wanted to show some form of support, however carrying attitudes such as those young ladies is what almost kept me from spending my money here. I will not be returning I'll go back to Rancho Cucamonga</Review>

<Name>Maya P.</Name><Date>1556472343194< /Date><rating>5<//rating><review>I am impressed as the food, decor, cleanliness, and service were excellent. I was originally looking for high quality, tasty, and well seasoned African food and this place was the closest one in the vicinity of where I was. It definitely lived up to the standard. The jerk chicken was  full of flavor without being overly salty, spicy  as she warned me (But I love spice and it was just enough heat that it was easily eatable), and tender. The rice/beans were the perfect texture and subtly spiced. The coco bread was great as well and was available to have singular or purchase by the pack. The spinach was fresh and sauteed perfectly without being overly oily. The beef/curry chicken patty were insanely good; homemade, spiced perfectly, large, and light flaky crust. I took a few to go to freeze. My family had the curry goat and jerk turkey burgers (How creative!) - they liked their food as well. I haven't had food like this in a long time and had to write this review since such a great job was done. To make food like this from scratch takes a lot of preparation and work, but above all, passion. And you can tell they had that and it was not rushed. The desserts looked good too, but I already had enough on my plate (no pun). But when I'm in the area again, I will try more options. 5/5 Stars.</review><pictures>None< /pictures><response>None< /response><gmapID>0x80c33205a3a9930f:0xb130487246c4b7dd<//gmapID></record></dataset><record>

< Review>
We had a disastrous experience with a return! My family and I shop mostly on line because of the pandemic. We have two small children. Sometimes items don't work out so we might need to return or exchange one item, never more than two. We have a gap card and love to earn points so we use it all the time. The 1st time returning they couldn't find our transaction. The second time they couldn't find our transaction and gave my husband a store credit. Went back the other day, and once again they couldn't find it! They never asked if we had a gap card, they assumed my husband bought it from an outlet! The only reason we were returning was because they sent us the wrong item, and charged us for the item ordered! They "assumed" we would only buy from outlet and didn't even bother to look for the transaction. We had our receipt in our email, but this mall blocks all signal when you are inside so we couldn't bring it up! I will never shop in this location again. I'm saddened that the Burlingame store closed. Horrible customer service! I even spoke to the store manager, and she knew exactly what she had done to my husband! So angry with them!< /Review>

< UserId.>
100028996223235852872</UserId.>
<Name>Mary Qi</Name>< Pics>
None<//Pics>
< review>
Karaoke the Asian way with private rooms! The interior is very basic with absolutely no frills or decor. Pricing is on a per-person basis (not per-room, unlike other establishments) and the rate differs depending on the day of the week and the hour. Weekend evenings are the most expensive. The "remote" used to search for and select songs are essentially tablets and can be super slow and unresponsive. The lady at the counter was kind enough to give us a second one that worked better after we asked for help. No alcohol is allowed in the rooms and, though the front desk sells some snacks (think potato chips), you are mostly on your own for food. Probably because of that, you are allowed to bring outside food in, so that's a huge plus! Song selection is amazing - probably the best of any karaoke place I've been to. Use the remote to look up artists and songs instead of toiling through the tomes of print-outs. They have a lot of recent songs still being played on the radio as well as songs from musicals (i.e. Hamilton, Wicked, Les Mis). When checking out, they were also nice enough to split the check for everyone. Gamba is a great option if you are looking to karaoke with friends.</review>

105250547903727145741< /user_id>
<user_name>Watson Tungjunyatham<//user_name><time>1512845783614</time>< rating>
5<//rating>
< Review>
tl;dr: One of the most authentic Japanese karaoke places in the local area.

For Japanese songs: Request Joysound or Livedam machines. As of this review, there is 1 Joysound machine and 3 Livedam machines. The Joysound is the HyperJOY Wave. Some Livedam machines are older than others. Be sure to check their respective websites to see if the song you want to sing is there (be prepared to type in Japanese).

Western songs typically use Healsonic software, whose song selections are OK at best, generally mediocre. It's truly the Japanese software that shines.

Honestly, it's not only because of the rates, but the really nice people running Gamba. They are truly a gem of the Japanese bay area community.

Whether you're learning Japanese or just want to chill and sing idol songs, Gamba is the place to go. Nico nico nii~< /Review>

None</Pics>

<rating>5</rating>< user_name>
Duc Pham<//user_name>
< Review>
Excellent private room karaoke place. They have updated their Japanese Joysound systems from HyperJoyv2 to HyperJoy Wave. This expands their Japanese library to have the latest Jpop and anime songs for you to sing. Their English database constantly expands to the latest music as well. The rooms are maintained well, and you can even order snacks to be delivered to your room. The prices are competitive, and if you go during their opening hours from 8AM to 2PM, it's only a dollar an hour per person!< /Review>

<name>Spencer Drennan<//name><text>I came here to get some bark for the yard. I was a little skeptical, since I'd never been here before, and I've had bad experiences before with industrial places treating me like an idiot. Anyway, I drove my little truck past the massive tractors and earthmoving machines and went into the office. The staff were very nice, helpful, and understanding. They have all their products on display in the office, and let you take free samples so that you get exactly what you need. They sell the material by the cubic yard. For scale, one yard of bark filled the bed of my 2002 Toyota Tundra up to the edge of the bed. They measure it using their tractor, which picks up the material a half yard at a time and drops it into the bed of the truck. So, I paid for my yard of material, and drove the truck over to what I had paid for. The reason I give 4 stars instead of 5 is that the office told me that "if the guys out there are doing their job, they'll stop you and come help you," but I ended up having to get their attention. Even so, I was able to pay and get my materials within 15 minutes, so I can't complain much. It is a great place.< /text>< Date>

<time>1548352286068</time>< text>
Sure at first great experience.. then you realize how bad this place is... don't get me wrong the instructor Rafael was FANTASTIC! gave us real world examples and taught  everyone in a very understandable way, however the staff are not so great.. Frida for example she's nice... sometimes mostly in a bad mood and gives attitude , Alexis is super nice, the other lady's well they're rude if your younger nice if your middle aged and one of the ladies is named Vanessa she is incredibly kind and helpful however a bit weird, she tries to set almost everyone up with her brother and asks about your personal love life too aside from that she's shares her life story With EVERYONE which sure okay is nice to hear about but rather annoying when you just want to apply...
The beds and other equipment DO NOT WORK they make a lot of money off of us and can't afford to buy new equipment for us to learn!? Seriously everyone is paying 1600 and that means we expect beds and stethoscopes that WORK!! besides that they scam you into spending as much money as possible... If you loose a paper booklet for example you have to pay for it... when they have a plethora of them... they say uniform is included when you first sit down to get information, however it's NOT you have to pay for it, they just "discount it" from the total balance, and if youh want to aign up for the review classes let me just say there is no refund and payment is in cash ONLY becuase they do it "under the table" meaning it goes to the school, and there are no reciets or files documented, aside from that if you are a spanish speaker and have trouble with English go somewhere else becuase this place does NOT offer the test in Spanish they just offer it in English and I know for a fact some colleges offer the test in Spanish aswell,  and let's not forget the ROACHES! if you want this career go to a college it's cheaper and better plus colleges give you more books and equipment and I'm sure their beds actually work... this place is not that great.... I'm sorry but I'm not going to sugar coat it I'm being honest with you, that way you don't waste your hard earned money on this place if it's not the best as they claim.. and a reminder you must pay 100 dollars a week, they took us by surprise and many were confused then they said "you signed it look we did tell you" let me just say what other students experienced aswell THEY DID NOT! <text>When I arrived at St. Jude for the first day of my CNA classes, I was expecting a very simple and boring 5 weeks (the length of one of the CNA classes offered). But from the moment the instructor started speaking, I knew that I was wrong.

St. Jude's Nursing School offers an unparalleled Certified Nursing Assistant (CNA) course that caters to the needs of the demanding medical field. With such fierce competition out there, it is very difficult to find a program that offers exemplary classes with a very affordable cost.

The classes are very informative, the learning environment is very inviting, and no one is ever left behind. The instructor, Maricela, is a kind woman who will help you through any topics that you're struggling with. The administrative staff welcomes anyone who steps foot into the school with a warm greeting. You will never feel out of place.

I found out about St. Jude Nursing school through a friend who also completed their CNA program recently. I would gladly spread the word about St. Jude to anyone who is looking for a job as a CNA.</text>< pictures>
